#FDA supports coordinated disclosure and applauds Medtronic for disclosing vulnerabilities in their medical devices. When device companies disclose their vulnerabilities, patients, clinicians, and hospitals are informed and better protected.

FDA isn’t aware of reports of patient harm related to these vulnerabilities. Like all technology, medical devices have vulnerabilities. Disclosing vulnerabilities to patients is a sign that companies take cybersecurity seriously.

FDA recommends providers and patients keep using these devices as intended. Medtronic is developing updates to further mitigate the vulnerabilities beyond devices’ design features that help safeguard patients. https:// go.usa.gov/xEtcj
